flowRoot.flowPara: Pluto was discovered by Clyde Tombaugh in 1930 and was originally considered to be the ninth planet from the Sun. After 1992, its status as a planet was questioned following the discovery of several objects of similar size in the Kuiper belt.
This is an experiment in using consistent rules for popover usage, as well as consistent styles for lists of items and lists of actions.
- Popovers only have a point if they are in reference to a discrete point
- Lists of options always have a white background
- Lists of actions/menu items always have the standard grey background
This is cheating slightly, since "edit labels" is an action and not an item to be selected. However, it is far simpler visually than having a hybrid of white list + grey menu actions.

One alternative would be to use radio buttons for options lists. In deciding about this, it's worth separating styling from control presentation/logic - we can style the popover background and the radio buttons however we want.
